The Cross River state House of Assembly has approved N16billion for the state governor, Ben Ayade, to spend on entertainment, assistance and contingency, as contained in the state’s 2019 budget. The breakdown shows that hospitality and entertainment will gulp N6billion, financial assistance N6billion while the governor is expected to spend N4billion on contingency. This follows their recent consideration of the state government’s N1.3 trillion 2019 budget tagged “Budget of Quabalistic Densification” which was announced last year by the governor. The sum of N7billion was also allocated for security; same amount was allocated in 2018. The assembly has passed the budget into law, Daily Trust reports. Ayade presents N1.043 trillion “budget of Quabalistic Densification” Gov Ayade appoints self oil commissioner,  to send envoys abroad Ayade releases N114m for 33 micro projects Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin